Police  were on Sunday at the state capture commission's offices in Parktown in Johannesburg after  a  reported burglary. An eyewitness, Mogamad Slamdien, told TimesLIVE that police were  on the scene and had sealed off access to the Hillside House building in Parktown on Sunday after a break-in on Saturday night. Slamdien said it was understood that electronic equipment, including computers, were taken from the office where the judicial commission of inquiry into allegations of state capture, headed by deputy chief justice Raymond Zondo, is sitting. The commission's Reverend Mbuyiselo Stemela said it would issue a statement shortly This is a developing story. TimesLIVE